-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Barwa, Oman International, Shuaa Capital
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-05-01T10:35:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-01/persian-gulf-stocks-barwa-oman-international-shuaa-capital.html
The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  decreased for a
fifth day, declining 0.5 percent at the 2 p.m. close in the
emirate. Qatar’s  QE Index (DSM)  decreased 0.4 percent while  Abu
Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  gained less than 0.1 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Barwa Real Estate Co. (BRES)   fell 2.9 percent to 27.1
riyals, to the lowest since February 2010. The Qatari property
company said first-quarter profit plunged 47 percent to 292.5
million riyals ($80 million).  Oman International Bank SAOG (OIBB)   slumped to the
lowest since February 2009, losing 7.6 percent to 0.232 rial.
The company, which is merging its operations with  HSBC Holdings
Plc (HSBA) , posted a 45 percent decline in first-quarter profit as
provisions for loan impairments rose.  Shuaa Capital PSC (SHUAA)   advanced the most since March
11, rising 4.6 percent to 79.5 fils. The investment bank
controlled by Dubai’s ruler plans to improve operating cash flow
by 71 percent in the first half as a result of a “rightsizing
progam” it began last year.  Zad Holding (ZHCD)   surged 9.9 percent, the biggest gain
in more than three years, to 57.7 riyals. The Qatari foods
company and wheat importer said first-quarter profit rose to
41.6 million riyals from 35.4 million in the year earlier
period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
